  "informal_statement": "For every real x ≥ 2, ∫_2^x (log t + 1)/(t log² t) dt = (log log x − 1/log x) − (log log 2 − 1/log 2).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "The integrand is the exact derivative of t ↦ log log t − 1/log t; verify the derivative pointwise on [2, x] and apply the fundamental theorem of calculus for interval integrals.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem mertens_main_term_antiderivative :\n    ∀ x : ℝ, 2 ≤ x →\n      ∫ t in (2:ℝ)..x, (Real.log t + 1) / (t * (Real.log t)^2)\n        = (Real.log (Real.log x) - (Real.log x)⁻¹)\n          - (Real.log (Real.log 2) - (Real.log 2)⁻¹)",
